{
  "stem": "3874.2",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "May your luck shine, and be as bright as the stars in heaven, and may it be written in our future to be able to hold you in our arms and make life again nicer for you, as we have always strived to do.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You alone are our total longing and hope.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And therefore, you must remain healthy, big, and strong.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In my thoughts, I lift my hands over your head, and bless you with a blessing from the Bible.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "May God bless you, shelter, and protect you, and always hold his right hand over you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Amen.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We are healthy, well.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Again, with the most urgent wishes to see you again in peace and joy, I embrace you and kiss you many thousand times.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Your always faithful, Papa.' It's a very moving letter, now that I-- now that I'm grown.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At the time, I did not recognize all the implications of it, but it was probably the last letter that he's ever written.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, that was written, of course, after I came to the United States.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In the meantime, I was still in France, and life continued over there, at Chateau Montintin.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We-- we did go to school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My carpentry skills improved.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We started learning English.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And what the OSE tried to do, is they tried getting the children out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Which, I think I've said it before.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "In the meantime, amongst the things that have occurred, the-- in the United States, there was a movement to get some of the children to the-- to the United States.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The joint committee, along with Eleanor Roosevelt, the American Quakers, and, from Chicago, there was the magnate, Marshall Fields-- somehow, I'm reading history, but those are the organizations that were responsible of trying to get children to the United States.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
